Problem¶

For international travelers, driving in unfamiliar countries can pose significant challenges, particularly when confronted with diverse traffic signals and road signage. Misinterpreting these visual cues can lead to accidents, fines, and even legal repercussions.

Targeted Resolution¶

In this project, we will use Convolutional Neural Network to build train and test a traffic sign classification model. We will build this model using tensorflow and keras. It is a multiclass classification problem. This model can be used to make smarter cars.

# Now we will reshape the images to (50,50)
images = []
label_id = []

for i in range(43):
    labels = 'traffic_sign_dataset/Train' + '/{0}'.format(i)
    image_path = os.listdir(labels)
    for x in image_path:
        img = Image.open(labels + '/' + x)
        img = img.resize((50,50))
        img = np.array(img)
        images.append(img)
        label_id.append(i)

############################### Model 2 ##############################################################

model = Sequential()

# First convolutional block
model.add(Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), input_shape=x_train.shape[1:], activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

# Second convolutional block with more filters
model.add(Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

# Third convolutional block to capture more features
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

# This layer converts the 3D feature maps from CNN into a 1D vector so that it can be passed to the fully connected layers.
model.add(Flatten())

# Fully connected layer with more neurons
model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

# Output layer for classification
model.add(Dense(43, activation='softmax'))

Function to Preprocess Test Images¶

We need to define a function that will load, resize, and scale the images from the test dataset.

In [128]:
def scaling(test_images, test_path):
    images = []
    image_path = test_images
    
    # Loop through each image and preprocess it
    for x in image_path:
        img = Image.open(test_path + '/' + x)
        img = img.resize((50,50))  # Resizing images to 50x50
        img = np.array(img)
        images.append(img)
    
    # Convert images to numpy array and scale pixel values
    images = np.array(images)
    images = images / 255  # Normalize pixel values between 0 and 1
    
    return images

Now, we will preprocess the images by calling the scaling function, which resizes and normalizes the images to make them ready for prediction.

precision = {}

    precision[i], recall[i], _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true == i, y_pred == i)

ROC Curve and AUC Score¶

In [135]:
# Binarize the labels for ROC curve (multi-class)
y_true_bin = label_binarize(y_true, classes=range(len(all_labels)))
y_pred_bin = label_binarize(y_pred, classes=range(len(all_labels)))

# Compute ROC curve and AUC for each class
fpr, tpr, roc_auc = {}, {}, {}
for i in range(len(all_labels)):
    fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_true_bin[:, i], y_pred_bin[:, i])
    roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

# Plot ROC curve
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 15))
for i in range(len(all_labels)):
    plt.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label=f'Class {all_labels[i]} (AUC = {roc_auc[i]:.2f})')

# Plot random chance line (diagonal)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='gray', linestyle='--')

plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve for each class')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

Conclusion:¶

We started with downloading the dataset, preprocessing it, created the model and found out the predictions using the model. During preprocessing we found that this dataset has 43 classes. Model reached an accuracy of 95%+ in just 10 epochs, we can further optimize the model using hyper parameter tuning and reach a higher accuracy.

Scope:¶

This model can be used in self driving cars which will enable them to automatically recognize traffic signs similarly the driver alert system inside cars will help and protect drivers by understanding the traffic signs around them.
